<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> put something in hand • take something in hand</xh5><p> <i>put something in hand—</i>undertake a task; begin work on smth.: We have <u>put the work in hand</u>, and it should be completed within the next week.</p><p> <i>take something in hand—</i>1. <i>= put something in hand:</i> We are just now <u>taking in hand</u> a massive program for the redevelopment of the city center. 2. take charge or control of smth.: She was no business woman, and until her son <u>took them in hand</u>, her affairs were chaotic.</p> </entry>
